comments:
Eclipse 3.1.1 M20050929-0840, Sun 1.5.0_03-b07, Win XP SP2

Internal Compiler Error while compiling the following 3 classes :

==============================================
package bug;

public class BugBase<T extends BugBase> {
}
==============================================
package bug;

public class BugParent extends BugBase<BugChild> {
}
==============================================
package bug;

public class BugChild extends BugParent implements Comparable<BugChild> {

    public int compareTo(BugChild o) {
        return 0;
    }
}
==============================================

The error also appears with open declaration (F3 key) on "(BugParent extends)
BugBase".
If "implements Comparable<BugChild>" is commented out, the project will build
correctly. Decommenting it will leave the project in an error-free state.
Cleaning and building the project will give the error again.

Problem occurs while connecting supertypes. Not enough info is available for
checking interface collisions.
It feels the interface collisions check should be extracted outside
#connectSuperInterfaces() and be called in sequence when connecting type
hierarchies, since the #connectSuperInterfaces() can be triggered independantly
through hierarchy cycle check (when hierarchy is only partially connected).
*** Bug 132012 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Created an attachment (id=36848)
Big testcase showing the error.

To get the error add the "src" folder as a source-folder. Then open BaseGame.java and try to invoke the Type-name-Helper. The testcase is rather big, but while I removed all the content of the classes I sometimes experienced that the Bug did not show up.
